# Fraunhofer R&D Targeting Automation

## Purpose

Identify optimal target customers (Korean government ministries / private companies) for Fraunhofer commissioned research and their strategic needs from collected articles.

## Scope & Filtering

- **Geography:** Analysis focus is **Republic of Korea only**. Foreign articles are excluded at collection/filter stage (`korea_scope.py`).
- **Targets:** Government budget holders and technology-demand companies.
- **Priority signals:** Articles mentioning investment, budget, collaboration, roadmap, technology acquisition — not pure tech news without investment plans.
- **Drop at filter:** Personal career/credential pieces (기술사·자격증 합격 인터뷰, 현장체험·진로 프로그램) and research-outcome-only items with no funder signal — even if a monitoring keyword appears (`rd_targeting.is_excluded_rd_news`).
- **Fact-only:** Extract amounts, program periods, required technologies from source text. No subjective judgment.

## Required Output Structure (per item)

1. **투자 주체** — Ministry / company name investing or needing technology (source fact only)
2. **투자 목적** — Localization, internalization, upgrade, time compression, capability gap (source fact only)
3. **팩트 근거 / 원문 인용** — Prefer 「」 verbatim quotes from press/article/paper; never invent absent numbers/names
4. **위탁 연구 니즈** — High-difficulty R&D pain points — label `(의견)` on its own line
5. **접근 전략** — Government: policy alignment; Company: roadmap linkage — label `(의견)` on its own line

Implemented in `summarizer.py` → `ko_summary_steps` headings and rendered in `daily_report.py` as **R&D 타겟팅 (프라운호퍼)** block + daily **국내 R&D 타겟 시사점** section.

Fact-check: no invented content; maximize direct quotes; keep mere opinion on separate `(의견)` lines.

## Sorting Priority

`rd_targeting.investment_signal_score` + `policy_priority_score` boost items with budget/investment/R&D signals and Korean actors in daily report ordering.
